[gd_scene load_steps=35 format=3]

; Dev-only greybox for the task-06 manual playtest (F6). Not wired into GameManager — mission flow is
; task 11. Each obstacle is an Obstacle (Interactable) Node3D with a StaticBody3D collider child, so the
; player's interaction ray resolves it. The "Debug" node adds a crosshair + a live [F]-prompt line (the
; label reads the real InputMap binding, so it stays correct even if "interact" is rebound) and floats a
; state tag over each obstacle (real HUD is task 15). Move with WASD, look with the mouse, aim the + and
; press/HOLD [F] — NOT E: E/Q are lean_right/lean_left (peek), a separate action. Fully operable now
; (no task 07/08 needed):
;   * FUSE BOX (yellow, zone "wing_a"): HOLD F to cut power — the e-lock (OPENS) and camera (OFF) drop
;     out. It deliberately does NOT reach the laser (different zone) — proving power cuts are
;     zone-scoped (FR-06-8), not global.
;   * JUNCTION BOX (orange, zone "vault" — same FuseBox script, just the laser's zone): HOLD F to cut
;     THIS one instead and watch the red LASER go dark (armed -> OFF). This is the laser's
;     "disable at a junction box" counter-play (FR-06-6).
;   * E-LOCK (cyan): tap F to start a hack, then STAY CLOSE — it fills over ~3s and OPENS; walk out of
;     range and it pauses, step back and it resumes.
; Props pending downstream systems (labelled on their tag): LOCK + SAFE need the task-07 minigame
; overlay; the KEYCARD DOOR needs a held card (task 08); the laser's other counter-plays (reveal via
; Thief Vision/aerosol, EMP) need their gadgets (tasks 08/09). Their counter-play logic is
; unit-tested + data-driven.

